To reiterate, the best demonstration of #Bitcoin as a strong SOV is significantly higher low created from each cycle.  With each cycle, the % decrease from the ATH is lowering, consistent with all preceding networks before it (i.e. Amazon).

The capabilities for #Bitcoin has never been better and investment in the protocol has never been higher.  The volatility of the price is not an indictment of #Bitcoin's properties as a strong SOV; rather, it is merely an outcome of any network related protocol.

Many cite that #Bitcoin has proven to be a SOV if you just zoom out... price going from $1 in April 2011 to $29k 2day.  Critics will concede this but believe it has Ponzi-like, or more appropriately, fad-like qualities where demand will eventually dissipate & price will plummet.

I believe this #Bitcoin cycle is the most important period to provide much greater conviction to Bitcoin as a SOV.  I often refer to #Bitcoin as an emerging SOV dependent on ongoing user/government/corporate adoption and further proof the protocol is indestructible.
